# ============================================================================
# Section 2.  Conventions and Definitions
# ============================================================================

  (append after the BCP 14 paragraph)

+ This document uses the terminology of the SCHC Architecture
+ [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture]: Endpoint, Instance, Instance
+ Configuration, Context, Set of Rules (SoR), Set of Variables (SoV),
+ Rule, RuleID, Session, Domain, Dispatcher, and Discriminator.  A
+ physical device may host a SCHC Endpoint, which in turn hosts one or
+ more SCHC Instances; a Session is a communication among two or more
+ Instances that share a common Context.  In this document, "SCHC
+ Gateway" and "SCHC Proxy" designate network-side and intermediate
+ hosts, respectively, each hosting a SCHC Endpoint.

