+ The Figure 10 shows a high-level configuration of the network
+ communication between a Device and an Application Server (App).  The
+ Dev, the Proxy, and the Application Server each host a SCHC Endpoint.
+ The Dev has short-lived intermittent connections and needs a middle
+ host called the SCHC Proxy, whose Instances participate in two
+ Sessions that share the same Context (i.e., belong to the same
+ Domain): one Session with the Instance of the Dev and one Session
+ with the Instance of the Application Server.  The Proxy maintains the
+ Session state (Set of Variables) even if the communication is
+ discontinued with the Dev, while communication continues with the
+ Application Server.  The Proxy may answer some requests instead of
+ the Dev.

