# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Section 4.4.1.  LEO Satellite as a SCHC Proxy
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

- In this mechanism, the LEO satellite has the function of SCHC proxy.
- The SCHC proxy has two features to improve SCHC performance with
- local acknowledgments and retransmissions.  These messages are
- employed to trigger local (and faster) error recovery.  In both
- communication directions, it is recommended to use the fragmentation
- mode assigned by each profile.
+ In this mechanism, the LEO satellite hosts a SCHC Endpoint acting as
+ a SCHC Proxy.  The SCHC Proxy has two features to improve SCHC
+ performance with local acknowledgments and retransmissions.  These
+ messages are employed to trigger local (and faster) error recovery.
+ In both communication directions, it is recommended to use the
+ fragmentation mode assigned by each profile.

- *  In uplink communications, the SCHC Proxy locally acknowledges SCHC
-    regular fragments with an SCHC ACK message.  Local acknowledgments
-    split the SCHC connection between the end-device and SCHC Gateway.
-    When local acknowledgments are used, the responsibility for
-    retrieving any fragments after the proxy SCHC has acknowledged
-    them lies with the proxy.
+ *  In uplink communications, the SCHC Proxy locally acknowledges SCHC
+    regular fragments with a SCHC ACK message.  Local acknowledgments
+    split the end-to-end SCHC exchange between the end-device and the
+    SCHC Gateway into two Sessions that share the same Context (i.e.,
+    belong to the same Domain): one Session between the Instance of
+    the end-device and the Instance of the SCHC Proxy, and one Session
+    between the Instance of the SCHC Proxy and the Instance of the
+    SCHC Gateway.  When local acknowledgments are used, the
+    responsibility for delivering any fragments that the SCHC Proxy
+    has acknowledged lies with the Proxy.  The local-acknowledgment
+    behavior itself is defined at profile level and is not an
+    architectural property of Sessions.

- *  In downlink communications, the SCHC Proxy retransmits locally the
-    regular SCHC fragments that losses between SCHC Proxy and end-
-    device.
+ *  In downlink communications, the SCHC Proxy retransmits locally the
+    SCHC regular fragments lost between the SCHC Proxy and the end-
+    device.

